description.plain:
Margaret Lindemann (July 21, 1998), better known as Maggie Lindemann, is an American singer-songwriter and internet celebrity. She’s known for her popularity on Instagram, from which she has over one million followers.

On 4 September 2015, her debut single “Knocking On Your Heart” was released.

She cites Lana Del Rey and Banks as musical influences.

songs.title: Pretty Girl

description.plain:
“Pretty Girl” is Maggie Lindemann’s fourth original song. It’s a catchy pop tune about what it’s like to be a young woman in this period of time.

On a March 17, 2017, interview with Billboard, Maggie spoke about how people overlooking her as a singer inspired her to write the song:

When people call me a social-media star, I feel looked past for being a singer. [“Pretty Girl”] is about being more than just what people see online and girls being more than our physical appearances. I think people need to look past just that and find what’s deeper.

This is Lindemann’s first major-label release. She’s signed to the Atlantic Records-owned imprint 300 Entertainment, home of Migos, Fetty Wap, and Young Thug, among others.

songs.title: Obsessed

description.plain:
“Obsessed” is the upbeat track follow-up to Maggie’s hit single “Pretty Girls”. The song was on November 17, 2017 through 300 Entertainment. The song is Maggie’s fifth original song and second major-label release.

The song is also has the same title of her beauty campaign with makeup artist Pat McGrath. Billboard asked her which came first and she replied with:

My song came first, and then we collaborated with Pat and came out with ‘So Obsessed.’ It wasn’t all thought of at once but then once the idea came up it would be really cool to release it with Spotify and release it with the single. We thought it would be a cool collaboration kind of idea."
